The paper presents a database of human faces, which is likely to be used for computer vision tasks such as face detection, eye detection, head tracking, and eye gaze tracking. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). The paper also mentions the potential use of the database for human-computer interaction (cs.HC), multimedia (cs.MM), information retrieval (cs.IR), and machine learning (cs.LG) tasks.
